ABUJA – Chief Philip Agbese, the member-elect representing Ado/Okpokwu/Ogbadibo Federal Constituency, and convener of the House of Representatives caucus, the Nationalists Forum has disclosed that the group will soon submit its zoning template for the 10th National Assembly to President-Elect, Asiwaju Bola Tinubu. The caucus, consisting of over 260 members (both new and old), disclosed this after a meeting on Tuesday, to adopt a zoning formula for principal offices, including Speakership. Chief Agbese said their template is in the interest of Nigeria and Nigerians. Agbese said after their inaugural meeting, Tuesday’s session in Abuja was for critical stakeholders with members agreeing on sharing the offices to reflect the geographical spread of the country. In a statement on Wednesday, Agbese hi red that they will seek an audience with the President-elect to submit their template to him. The group, which is made up of members drawn from different political parties, said they are out to galvanize the nation amid tribal, political, ethnic, and religious sentiments.The member-elect assured Nigerians that the best set of leaders will emerge to lead the House of Representatives. He described Asiwaju Tinubu as a thorough democrat, just as he expressed confidence that the President-elect will adopt the formula in the interest of the country.‒‒:‒‒/‒‒:‒‒ He added that what the nation needs at this crucial time is healing and not further division.